{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:Wiki Project Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:Wiki Project Books]] --> | name = Masters of Sex: The Life and Times of William Masters and Virginia Johnson, the Couple Who Taught America How to Love | image = File:Masters of Sex.jpg | caption = Cover of the first edition | author = [[Thomas Maier]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = [[Masters and Johnson]] | publisher = [[Basic Books]] | pub_date = 2009 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]] and [[Paperback]]) | pages = 440 | isbn = | dewey= | congress= | oclc= | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Masters of Sex: The Life and Times of William Masters and Virginia Johnson, the Couple Who Taught America How to Love''''' is a 2009 biography by [[Thomas Maier]]. The book chronicles the early lives and work of two American [[sexologist]]s, [[William Masters|Dr. William Masters]] and [[Virginia E. Johnson|Virginia Johnson]], who studied [[human sexuality]] from 1957 to the 1990s. The 2013 [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] television series ''[[Masters of Sex]]'', starring [[Michael Sheen]] and [[Lizzy Caplan]], is based on the book.<ref name=theguardian>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=PD|title=Masters of Sex by Thomas Maier – review|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2013/oct/11/masters-sex-thomas-maier-review|publisher=theguardian.com|accessdate=23 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=amazon>{{cite web|title=Masters of Sex: The Life and Times of William Masters and Virginia Johnson, the Couple Who Taught America How to Love Paperback – July 30, 2013|url=https://www.amazon.com/Masters-Sex-William-Virginia-Johnson/dp/0465079997|publisher=amazon.com|accessdate=23 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=b&n>{{cite web|title=Masters of Sex: The Life and Times of William Masters and Virginia Johnson, the Couple Who Taught America How to Love|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/masters-of-sex-thomas-maier/1100305060?ean=9780465079995|publisher=barnes