==Reception== The book had a positive reception. [[Debby Applegate]] described the biography as "a terrific book about the unlikely couple who touched off the [[sexual revolution]]. More than a biography, this is an intimate history of sex in the twentieth century." ''[[The New York Times]]'' commended Maier's writing style and sense of humor. The ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' named it as one of their favorite non-fiction books of 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=Our favorite nonfiction of 2009 - Printers Row|url=http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/printers-row/our-favorite-nonfiction-of-2009.html|accessdate=28 January 2014|newspaper=Chicago Tribune|date=4 December 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091213012153/http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/printers-row/our-favorite-nonfiction-of-2009.html|archivedate=13 December 2009}}</ref>
