{{Infobox non-profit | name =Société des designers graphiques du Québec |abbreviation = SDGQ | image = | caption = | map = | map_size = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | map_alt = <!-- map alt text --> | map_caption = | map2 = | type =Professional Association | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = --> | registration_id =1142549352<ref name=NEQ>{{cite web |url=http://www.registreentreprises.gouv.qc.ca/en/ |title=Registraire des entreprises |at=Find an entreprise (button), Société des designers graphiques du Québec (search term) |publisher=[[Revenu Québec]] |language=fr |trans-title=Business registry |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> | founded_date = {{start date|1974}}<ref name=ICOGRADA-enews-sdgq>{{cite journal |journal=enews |issn=1997-373X |url=http://www.icograda.org/newsletter/index/enews_issues14/enews_articles132.htm |title=Profile: SDGQ |date=April 3, 2008 |publisher=[[Icograda]] |accessdate=July 18, 2014}}</ref> | founder =Georges Beaupré, Roger Lafortune | predecessor = | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merged = | successor = | location =[[Montreal]] | addnl_location = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} --> | origins = | key_people =President Philippe Lamarre<ref name=SDGQ-ca>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/sdgq/profil/ca/ |title=C.A. |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=Board of directors |accessdate=July 16, 2014}}</ref> | area_served =[[Quebec]] | products = | services = | focus = | mission = | method = | revenue = | disbursed = | expenses = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees = | num_members = 300<ref name=Brooker2013/>{{rp|57}} | affiliations =[[Icograda]], CIDQ, Mission Design, CICQ<ref name=SGQ-affiliations>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/sdgq/profil/affiliations/ |title=Affiliations |author=SDGQ |language=fr |accessdate=July 16, 2014}}</ref> | subsid = | languages =[[French language|French]] | owner = | motto = | formerly =Société des graphistes du Québec (SGQ)<ref name=SDGQ-historique>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/sdgq/profil/historique/ |title=Historique |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=History |accessdate=July 16, 2014}}</ref> | website = {{url|sdgq.ca}} | footnotes = }} The '''{{lang|fr|Société des designers graphiques du Québec}} (SDGQ)''' is the provincial [[graphic design]] association in the Canadian province of [[Quebec]].<ref name=Brooker2013/>{{rp|57}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cicic.ca/en/professions.aspx?sortcode=2.19.21&prof=5241 |title=Information for foreign-trained graphic designers |website=[[Council of Ministers of Education, Canada|Canadian Information Centre for International Credentials]] |date=2011-10-18 |accessdate=July 15, 2014}}</ref>{{efn|Regarding GDC and RGD’s relationship, Brooker (2013) noted that “In 2003, the GDC cut the cord. Henceforth, graphic design organizations would trundle forward behind the standard Canadian troika: Ontario, Quebec and the rest of the country.”}} Its stated aim is to advance the profession of graphic design in Quebec and to help its members develop both professionally and financially.<ref name=ICOGRADA-sdgq>{{cite web |url=http://www.icograda.org/members/members/member_list73.htm |title=Société des designers graphiques du Québec |publisher=[[Icograda]] |accessdate=July 18, 2014}}</ref> Its activities include professional development, co-organizing the Grafika design awards competition, lobbying, and the DGA certification program.<ref name=Brooker2013/>{{rp|59}}{{efn|Brooker (2013) notes specifically that compared to the GDC and the RGD, “In Quebec, the SDGQ undertakes a similar scope of activities, despite its smaller size.}}
The SDGQ has a reconciliatory role in the debate on graphic design certification in Canada.<ref name=Brooker2013/>{{rp|59}}
==History== The history of the SDGQ can be traced back to 1972 when Quebec graphic designers, Georges Beaupré and Roger Lafortune,<ref name=SDGQ-historique/><ref name=Lapointe2014>{{cite journal |journal=Continuité |issue=141 |year=2014 |pages=50–52 |title=Identité graphique |first=Louis |last=Lapointe |language=fr |publisher=Éditions Continuité |url=http://id.erudit.org/iderudit/72096ac}}</ref>{{rp|51}} formed a committee to found the {{lang|fr|Société des graphistes du Québec}} (SGQ).<ref name=DG-historique/> However, SGQ was not officially founded until 1974<ref name=Brooker2013>{{cite journal |last=Brooker |first=Kevin |title=Professional Differences |journal=Applied Arts Magazine |volume=28 |issue=5 |date=November 2013 |pages=56–65 |url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=asu&AN=91936178&site=ehost-live |issn=1196-1775}}</ref><ref name=DG-historique>{{cite web |url=http://www.sdgq.ca/historique.php |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091225015014/http://www.sdgq.ca/historique.php |archivedate=December 25, 2009 |title=Historique |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=History |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref><ref name=MNBAQ2007>{{cite book |title=Québec in design |author=[[Musée national des beaux-arts du Québec]] |year=2007 |isbn=978-2-920496-04-0 |others=Translated by Käthe Roth |page=48}}</ref> when the new association was incorporated.<ref name=NEQ/> In 1995 the SGQ replaced the word “{{lang|fr|graphistes}}” (graphic designers or graphic artists) in its name with “{{lang|fr|designers graphiques}}” (graphic designers), changing its name to {{lang|fr|Société des designers graphiques du Québec}} (SDGQ).<ref name=NEQ/><ref name=SDGQ-historique/><ref name=Lapointe2014/>{{rp|51}}
On June 14, 2011, during its annual general meeting, the SDGQ officially launched its certification program for graphic designers in Quebec.<ref name=DG-dga>{{cite web |url=http://www.sdgq.ca/DGA/QA_DGA.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622075321/http://www.sdgq.ca/DGA/QA_DGA.html |archivedate=June 22, 2011 |title=Designer graphique agréé |first=Philippe |last=Lamarre |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref>
In 2013 the SDGQ adopted a new visual identity, replacing its existing “dg” [[wordmark]] with a new “SDGQ” wordmark.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/decouvrir/sdgq-nouveau-site-nouvelle-identite/ |title=SDGQ : Nouveau site, nouvelle identité |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=SGDQ: New site, new identity |accessdate=July 16, 2014}}</ref>
==Certification== SDGQ members working in the field of graphic design who have accumulated a minimum of 7 years of combined professional experience and education in graphic design can apply to be certified.<ref name=SDGQ-dga-qui>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/dga/qui/ |title=Qui peut devenir DGA |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=Who can become a DGA |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> Candidates are required to submit their portfolios to a panel of three DGA-certified judges for an anonymous review.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/dga/postuler/ |title=Postuler au titre du DGA |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=Apply for the DGA title |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> During the review, the candidate’s work is evaluated according to three criteria, namely, pertinence, responsibility, and creativity.<ref name=SDGQ-dga-qui/> Certified members are accredited with a {{lang|fr|Designer graphique agréé}}, DGA.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/decouvrir/dga-un-sceau-de-qualite/ |title=DGA : Un sceau de qualité |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=DGA: A seal of quality |accessdate=July 16, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gdc.net/article/2011/09/28/sdgq-introduces-certification-program-for-quebec-designers |title= SDGQ Introduces Certification Program for Quebec Designers |first=Marc |last=Serre |publisher=[[Society of Graphic Designers of Canada]] |date=September 28, 2011 |accessdate=July 16, 2014}}</ref>
DGAs are required to follow SDGQ’s code of ethics. There is a procedure in place to investigate DGAs who are accused of violating the code of ethics; violators can receive penalties up to and including having their DGA titles revoked.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/dga/responsabilites/ |title=Responsabilités du DGA |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=Responsibilities of the DGA |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref>
A plan to align the DGA and [[Association of Registered Graphic Designers|RGD]] certifications was announced in 2012,<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/story/934569/canadian-graphic-design-industry-takes-giant-step-forward |title=Canadian graphic design industry takes giant step forward |author=Association of Registered Graphic Designers |publisher=[[CNW Group]] |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref><ref name=RGD-partners/> and the written examination portion of the process was set to harmonize within 5 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rgd.ca/database/files/library/RGDandSDGQBipartiteAgreement_FR_1.pdf |title=La RGD et la SDGQ concluent un accord bipartite |first=Lionel |last=Gadoury |language=fr |trans-title=RGD and SDGQ reach bipartite agreement |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> The DGA title is considered by the Association of Registered Graphic Designers to be the French equivalent of its RGD title.<ref name=RGD-partners>{{cite web |url=http://www.rgd.ca/industry-partners.php |title=Partner Organizations |author=Association of Registered Graphic Designers |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref>
==Affiliations== SDGQ is a member of [[Icograda]], the {{lang|fr|Conférence interprofessionnelle du design du Québec}} (CIDQ), Mission Design, and the {{lang|fr|Conseil de l’industrie des communications de Québec}} (CICQ).<ref name="SGQ-affiliations"/> It also has formal partnerships with the [[Society of Graphic Designers of Canada]], the [[Association of Registered Graphic Designers]] of Ontario, and Infopress, a publishing company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/sdgq/profil/partenaires/ |title=Partenaires |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=Partners |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref>
==Publications== SDGQ has published two books, the ''{{lang|fr|Guide de gestion et de pratique professionnelle du designer graphique}}'' (the graphic designer’s guide to management and professional practice)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sdgq.ca/decouvrir/guide-de-gestion-et-de-pratique-professionnelle/ |title=Guide de gestion et de pratique professionnelle du designer graphique |author=SDGQ |language=fr |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> for graphic designers in Quebec, and ''{{lang|fr|Devenir designer graphique : guide sur l'éducation en design graphique au Québec}}'' (becoming a graphic designer: a guide to graphic design education in Quebec).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldcat.org/identities/nc-societe%20des%20designers%20graphiques%20du%20quebec/ |title=Société des designers graphiques du Québec |website=OCLC WorldCat Identities |publisher=[[OCLC]] |accessdate=July 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sdgq.ca/decouvrir/categorie/ressources/publication/ |title=Publication |author=SDGQ |language=fr |accessdate=July 18, 2014}}</ref>
SDGQ also publishes a blog called ''{{lang|fr|Œil pour œil}}'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sdgq.ca/sdgq/projets/ |title=Projets et initiatives |author=SDGQ |language=fr |trans-title=Projects and initiatives |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> which has entered a period of hiatus since 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://oeilpouroeil.ca/ |title=Œil pour œil |publisher=SDGQ |language=fr |accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Society of Graphic Designers of Canada]] * [[Association of Registered Graphic Designers]]
